      "title": "Module 2 — How the addiction reinforced the lie",
      "text": "Once nicotine was in the picture, the brainwashing got a powerful new ally: real chemical relief. Now every time you smoked under stress and felt the withdrawal lift, lived experience seemed to confirm the cultural story — \"see, it really does calm me.\" Belief and chemistry began reinforcing each other in a closed loop. The culture taught you what to expect; the drug produced a sensation; your mind filed the sensation under the expectation. Round and round, for years, until the belief felt less like an opinion and more like a fact of nature.\n\nThis is exactly why willpower-only quitting fails. Willpower attacks the chemistry — don't smoke, hold on, resist — while leaving the belief fully intact. And a belief you still hold will eventually find a weak moment to act on. We're doing it the other way: pull out the belief, and the craving has nothing left to stand on."
